    "body": "The `recovery` module is probably not super-relevant these days for newer projects (the primary use-case I'm aware of is message signing in Bitcoin Core and Electrum, likely other wallets; something that is hopefully replaced by [BIP-322](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0322.mediawiki) one day), but it still seems better to have an example than to have none. It contains all of the five API calls, i.e. for signing, recovering, converting, serializing, parsing. As usual with examples, a lot of code and comments are duplicated (e.g. context creation, keypair generation, cleanup with secret key clearing etc.).",
